{"title_page": "Palamagamba John Aidan Mwaluko Kabudi", "text_new": "{{Duplication}}\n\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix   = [[Honourable]]\n| name               = Professor Palamagamba John Aidan Mwaluko Kabudi\n| honorific-suffix   = [[Member of Parliament|MP]]\n| image              =   \n| office             = [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs and East African Cooperation]]\n| term_start         = 3 March 2019\n| term_end           = \n| president          = [[John Magufuli]]\n| predecessor        = [[Augustine Mahiga]]\n| successor          = \n| office2            = \n| term_start2        =\n| term_end2          = \n| minister2          =  \n| predecessor2       = \n| successor2         = \n| office3            = [[Member of Parliament (Tanzania)|Member of Parliament]]\n| term_start3        = 2015\n| term_end3          = \n| appointer3         = [[John Magufuli]]\n| constituency3      = None (Nominated MP)\n| birth_date         = 24 February 1956\n| birth_place        = \n| nationality        = Tanzanian\n| party              = \n| spouse             =  \n| alma_mater         = [[Freie Universit\u00e4t Berlin]] ([[PhD]])<br />[[University of Dar es Salaam]] ([[LLM]])<br />[[University of Dar es Salaam]] ([[LLB]])\n| religion           = \n| website            = \n}}\n\n'''Palamagamba John Aidan Mwaluko Kabudi ''' is a [[Tanzania]]n lawyer who currently serves as the country's Minister for Foreign Affairs and East African Cooperation appointed by [[President (government title)|President]] [[John Pombe Magufuli]].<ref>http://ikulu.go.tz/index.php/administration/about_biography/50</ref>\n\n== Early life and education ==\nKabudi was born on February 24, 1956 in [[Singida (town)|Singida]], [[Singida Region]]. He first attended Kilimatinde Primary school in 1964 then from 1965 to the end of 1966 he went to Kitete Primary school. In 1967 he finally transferred to Berega Primary School  before completing his CPEE at Mvumi Mission Primary School. In 1971 he joined The Tosamaganga Secondary School where he earned CSEE of Ordinary level education. From 1975 to 1976 he completed his ACSEE education at Milambo Secondary School. \n\nKabudi went to the [[University of Dar Es Salaam]] from 1980-1983 where he obtained his LLB. He furthered his studies in the same institution from 1984-1986 where he was awarded LLM. After that he attended [[Freie Universit\u00e4t Berlin]]  [[German language|German]] where he obtained a ([[Ph.D]]). in [[Law]],.<ref>http://www.fu-berlin.de/</ref>\n\n== Minister for Foreign Affairs and East African Cooperation ==\nIn 2019, Kabudi summoned Canada's [[Canadian High Commissions|High Commissioner]] Pamela O'Donnell to protest after a [[De Havilland Canada Dash 8|DHC Dash 8-400]] [[turboprop]], set to be delivered to state-owned [[Air Tanzania]] was impounded in a land compensation dispute.<ref>Fumbuka Ng'wanakilala (November 23, 2019), [https://www.reuters.com/article/us-tanzania-aviation/tanzania-protests-after-plane-seized-in-canada-over-land-compensation-dispute-idUSKBN1XX0GT Tanzania protests after plane seized in Canada over land compensation dispute] ''[[Reuters]]''.</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Cabinet of Tanzania}}\n{{Tanzanian Foreign Ministers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kabudi Palamagamba}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Chama Cha Mapinduzi MPs]]\n[[Category:Tanzanian MPs 2015\u20132020]]\n[[Category:Nominated Tanzanian MPs]]\n[[Category:1956 births]]\n[[Category:Foreign ministers of Tanzania]]\n\n\n{{Tanzania-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Duplication}}\n\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix   = [[Honourable]]\n| name               = Professor Palamagamba John Aidan Mwaluko Kabudi\n| honorific-suffix   = [[Member of Parliament|MP]]\n| image              =   \n| office             = [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs and East African Cooperation]]\n| term_start         = 3 March 2019\n| term_end           = \n| president          = [[John Magufuli]]\n| predecessor        = [[Augustine Mahiga]]\n| successor          = \n| office2            = \n| term_start2        =\n| term_end2          = \n| minister2          =  \n| predecessor2       = \n| successor2         = \n| office3            = [[Member of Parliament (Tanzania)|Member of Parliament]]\n| term_start3        = 2015\n| term_end3          = \n| appointer3         = [[John Magufuli]]\n| constituency3      = None (Nominated MP)\n| birth_date         = 24 February 1956\n| birth_place        = \n| nationality        = Tanzanian\n| party              = \n| spouse             =  \n| alma_mater         = [[Freie Universit\u00e4t Berlin]] ([[PhD]])<br />[[University of Dar es Salaam]] ([[LLM]])<br />[[University of Dar es Salaam]] ([[LLB]])\n| religion           = \n| website            = \n}}\n\n'''Palamagamba John Aidan Mwaluko Kabudi ''' is a [[Tanzania]]n lawyer who currently serves as the country's Minister for Foreign Affairs and East African Cooperation appointed by [[President (government title)|President]] [[John Pombe Magufuli]].<ref>http://ikulu.go.tz/index.php/administration/about_biography/50</ref>\n\n== Early life and education ==\nKabudi was born on February 24, 1956 in [[Singida (town)|Singida]], [[Singida Region]]. He first attended Kilimatinde Primary school in 1964 then from 1965 to the end of 1966 he went to Kitete Primary school. In 1967 he finally transferred to Berega Primary School  before completing his CPEE at Mvumi Mission Primary School. In 1971 he joined The Tosamaganga Secondary School where he earned CSEE of Ordinary level education. From 1975 to 1976 he completed his ACSEE education at Milambo Secondary School. \n\nKabudi went to the [[University of Dar Es Salaam]] from 1980-1983 where he obtained his LLB. He furthered his studies in the same institution from 1984-1986 where he was awarded LLM. After that he attended [[Freie Universit\u00e4t Berlin]]  [[German language|German]] where he obtained a ([[Ph.D]]). in [[Law]],.<ref>http://www.fu-berlin.de/</ref>\n\n== Minister for Foreign Affairs and East African Cooperation ==\nIn 2019, Kabudi summoned Canada\u2019s [[Canadian High Commissions|High Commissioner]] Pamela O'Donnell to protest after a [[De Havilland Canada Dash 8|DHC Dash 8-400]] [[turboprop]], set to be delivered to state-owned [[Air Tanzania]] was impounded in a land compensation dispute.<ref>Fumbuka Ng'wanakilala (November 23, 2019), [https://www.reuters.com/article/us-tanzania-aviation/tanzania-protests-after-plane-seized-in-canada-over-land-compensation-dispute-idUSKBN1XX0GT Tanzania protests after plane seized in Canada over land compensation dispute] ''[[Reuters]]''.</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Cabinet of Tanzania}}\n{{Tanzanian Foreign Ministers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kabudi Palamagamba}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Chama Cha Mapinduzi MPs]]\n[[Category:Tanzanian MPs 2015\u20132020]]\n[[Category:Nominated Tanzanian MPs]]\n[[Category:1956 births]]\n[[Category:Foreign ministers of Tanzania]]\n\n\n{{Tanzania-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eMinister for Foreign Affairs and East African Cooperation:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: \u2019s \u2192 's", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palamagamba_John_Aidan_Mwaluko_Kabudi"}
{"title_page": "Yahya Kassim Issa", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|honorific-prefix   = [[Honourable]]\n|name               = Yahya Kassim Issa\n|honorific-suffix   = [[Member of Parliament|MP]]\n|image              = \n|imagesize          = \n|alt                = \n|caption            = \n|order              = \n|office             = [[Member of Parliament (Tanzania)|Member of Parliament]] <br> for [[Chwaka]]\n|term_start         = November 1995\n|term_end           =\n|predecessor        = \n|successor          = \n|order2             =  \n|office2            = \n|term_start2        = \n|term_end2          = \n|predecessor2       =\n|successor2         =\n|birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1950|9|25|df=y}}\n|birth_place        = [[Sultanate of Zanzibar]]\n|birthname          = \n|nationality        = [[Tanzania]]n\n|party              = [[Chama Cha Mapinduzi|CCM]]\n|spouse             = \n|relations          = \n|children           = \n|residence          = \n|alma_mater         = \n|occupation         = \n|profession         = \n|religion           = \n|website            = \n|footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Yahya Kassim Issa''' (born 25 September 1950) is a [[Tanzania]]n [[Chama Cha Mapinduzi|CCM]] politician and [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Chwaka]] constituency since 2000.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.parliament.go.tz/index.php/members/mpcvs/1092/2010-2015 |title=Member of Parliament CV |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date=2010 |website= |publisher=[[Parliament of Tanzania]] |accessdate=25 October 2013}}</ref> Issa was originally a teacher from 1974\u20131982, and moved up in rank in the Ministry of Education, becoming a section leader in 1975, a headmaster in 1984, and a district education inspector in 1991. He arrived at his current position in 1995.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n{{Current CCM MPs}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Issa, Yahya Kassim}}\n[[Category:1950 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Chama Cha Mapinduzi MPs]]\n[[Category:Tanzanian MPs 2010\u20132015]]\n\n\n{{Tanzania-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|honorific-prefix   = [[Honourable]]\n|name               = Yahya Kassim Issa\n|honorific-suffix   = [[Member of Parliament|MP]]\n|image              = \n|imagesize          = \n|alt                = \n|caption            = \n|order              = \n|office             = [[Member of Parliament (Tanzania)|Member of Parliament]] <br> for [[Chwaka]]\n|term_start         = November 1995\n|term_end           =\n|predecessor        = \n|successor          = \n|order2             =  \n|office2            = \n|term_start2        = \n|term_end2          = \n|predecessor2       =\n|successor2         =\n|birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1950|9|25|df=y}}\n|birth_place        = [[Sultanate of Zanzibar]]\n|birthname          = \n|nationality        = [[Tanzania]]n\n|party              = [[Chama Cha Mapinduzi|CCM]]\n|spouse             = \n|relations          = \n|children           = \n|residence          = \n|alma_mater         = \n|occupation         = \n|profession         = \n|religion           = \n|website            = \n|footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Yahya Kassim Issa''' (born 25 September 1950) is a [[Tanzania]]n [[Chama Cha Mapinduzi|CCM]] politician and [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Chwaka]] constituency since 2000.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.parliament.go.tz/index.php/members/mpcvs/1092/2010-2015 |title=Member of Parliament CV |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date=2010 |website= |publisher=[[Parliament of Tanzania]] |accessdate=25 October 2013}}</ref> Issa was originally a teacher from 1974-1982, and moved up in rank in the Ministry of Education, becoming a section leader in 1975, a headmaster in 1984, and a district education inspector in 1991. He arrived at his current position in 1995.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n{{Current CCM MPs}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Issa, Yahya Kassim}}\n[[Category:1950 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[